Commentary: oh, dear. Heartbreak for Afghanistan! Rahmat Shah has chopped on and his maiden Test century, and Afghanistan's first, will have to wait! Commentary: oooh, he's got the worst luck! Missed his century in the first innings by two runs. Falls with Afghanistan three away from a historic win. Poor Rahmat. He did all the hard work and now with the target one hit away, he goes for that one hit, running down the track and being deceived by the change in length from Cameron-Dow. Swings wildly anyway, all across the line, is beaten by the turn and stumped fairly easily
Commentary_short: Cameron-Dow to Rahmat Shah, OUT
Dismissal_text: Rahmat Shah st †Poynter b Cameron-Dow 76 (122b 13x4 0x6) SR: 62.29

Commentary: he's run-out! Oooh, this is silly. And he knows it is, walking back, hitting the air with his bat. Having played a deft little sweep shot, he gets greedy and wants two. Fine leg runs back and to his left quickly enough to stop that and the throw at the strikers' end is pin-point too.
Commentary_short: Cameron-Dow to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run, OUT

Commentary: a rasping pull shot over square leg, racing away to the boundary and Shahidi will go down in history as the man who struck the runs that brought Afghanistan's first Test match victory. Punches the air in triumph, goes over to hug his partner, Ihsanullah, and they both soak in the moment.
Commentary_short: Cameron-Dow to Hashmatullah Shahidi, FOUR runs
